The difference will never be noticeable with bluetooth earbuds, you need a wired headset for it, which I will never use outside of my home.

I currently use both (I am deciding between them) I have some extra points to add to yours that I think are important for people to know:
1- Spotify has more nieche/nerdy and smaller-artist music. Videogame music and less coventional music tend to be missing from Apple music, espacially since it is way easier for smaller artists to upload their work to spotify than Apple Music.
2- It felt very lonely and isolating while listening to music on Apple Music. There is no community feel. I don't know what the people I follow listen to, I can't look up weird words and phrases and expect playlists to pop up. There are playlists that my favourite artists update every now and then that I'm not privy to immediatly accessing anymore. It all feels so lonely. you diffenetly get FOMO. espacially when Spotify Wrapped comes around.
3. It's not just headphones, some devices and phones do not support Lossless.
4. Apple music deletes your library adter a period of inactivity (not paying for their services)
I also want to add that even with crappy bluetooth headphones the audio difference is very much evident. I did not know Apple music offered better quality music. I stumbled upon it.

Sabrine Carpenter seems to be a well grounded and balanced young woman.

She also appears to have a very sane point of view about her young career as a singer and to have very close ties with her family.

She probably learned a lot from the strange path taken by so many other former Disney mascots before her who ended up with an oversexualized image that damaged their lives and carrers forever.

The fact she skyrocketed international fame at the age of 25 with Espresso and not at 15 or 16 like Spears, Lohan, and Aguilera is so much better for her future.

I am curious to see what she will do in the coming months and years.
